<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
    <h1>List Group</h1>
    <p class="text-muted">
      A "List Group" is a vertically stacked set of "items" which are contextually grouped in some way. The main property that can be set at the group level is whether the list items should be {{ui-pill 'selectable'}}. This is available as the boolean property and when set to <i>true</i> (the default) it will change the HTML from an unordered list (aka, &lt;UL>) of items to a set of links (aka, &lt;a>). Stylistically they will look the same but now a hover effect indicates that selectability is an option.
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted">
      The {{ui-label 'ui-list-group'}} component <i>yields</i> a {{ui-label 'ui-list-item'}} component as the 'item' property and this is where most of the configuration will exist. The <b>item</b> component exposes the following properties:
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted">
      <ul>
        <li><b>active</b> - boolean flag to indicate whether considered "active"</li>
        <li><b>disabled</b> - boolean flag to mark as disabled</li>
        <li><b>mood</b> - you can specify a color mood for the item (aka, 'success', 'danger', etc.)</li>
        <li><b>pill</b> - puts a pill component into the right hand side of the item</li>
        <li><b>label</b> - puts a label component into the right hand side of the item</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p class='text-muted'>
      The {{ui-label 'ui-list-item'}} component also <i>yields</i> the following contextual components:
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted">
      <ul>
        <li><b>item</b> - the main textual description</li>
        <li><b>heading</b> - optionally include a bigger heading text to the item (used with 'item')</li>
        <li><b>right</b> - to target the right side of the item use this component</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
{{#code-block language='handlebars'}}\{{#ui-list-group selectable=false as |list|}}
  \{{list.item 'Inbox' pill='6' pillMood='success'}}
